Fix the `sessionCreator` in `adapter-manager.ts` that currently passes `permissionMode: 'auto'` (an invalid value) to `ensureSession()`. Update it to accept the permission mode from the `AgentSessionCreator` interface and pass it through.

**Problem:**

In `apps/server/src/services/relay/adapter-manager.ts`, the `initBindingSubsystem()` method creates a `sessionCreator` with hardcoded `permissionMode: 'auto'`:

```typescript
const sessionCreator: AgentSessionCreator = {
  async createSession(cwd: string) {
    const id = crypto.randomUUID();
    agentManager.ensureSession(id, { permissionMode: 'auto', cwd });
    return { id };
  },
};
```

`'auto'` is not a valid value in `PermissionModeSchema` which defines `['default', 'plan', 'acceptEdits', 'bypassPermissions']`.

**Implementation Steps:**

1. Import the `PermissionMode` type:

```typescript
import type { PermissionMode } from '@dorkos/shared/schemas';
```

2. Update the `sessionCreator` to accept and pass through the permission mode:

```typescript
const sessionCreator: AgentSessionCreator = {
  async createSession(cwd: string, permissionMode?: PermissionMode) {
    const id = crypto.randomUUID();
    agentManager.ensureSession(id, {
      permissionMode: permissionMode ?? 'acceptEdits',
      cwd,
    });
    return { id };
  },
};
```

This fixes the bug by:
- Accepting the binding's `permissionMode` from the router (Task 1.3)
- Falling back to `'acceptEdits'` instead of the invalid `'auto'`
- Both values are valid `PermissionMode` enum members

**Verification:**

- `pnpm typecheck` should pass (if it wasn't catching the `'auto'` issue before, verify that `ensureSession` accepts `PermissionMode` type for its `permissionMode` parameter).
- Manually verify by searching for any other occurrences of `permissionMode: 'auto'` in the codebase and fixing them if found.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] `sessionCreator.createSession` accepts optional `permissionMode` parameter matching updated `AgentSessionCreator` interface
- [ ] `permissionMode: 'auto'` is replaced with `permissionMode: permissionMode ?? 'acceptEdits'`
- [ ] No occurrences of `permissionMode: 'auto'` remain in the codebase
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes
- [ ] `pnpm test -- --run` passes (no existing tests broken)

Add `permissionMode` to the `BindingFormValues` interface, add state management for it in `BindingDialog`, and include it in the form submission payload.

**File:** `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/ui/BindingDialog.tsx`

**Implementation Steps:**

1. **Import `PermissionMode` type:**

```typescript
import type { SessionStrategy } from '@dorkos/shared/relay-schemas';
import type { PermissionMode } from '@dorkos/shared/schemas';
```

2. **Add `permissionMode` to `BindingFormValues`:**

```typescript
export interface BindingFormValues {
  adapterId: string;
  agentId: string;
  sessionStrategy: SessionStrategy;
  label: string;
  chatId?: string;
  channelType?: 'dm' | 'group' | 'channel' | 'thread';
  permissionMode?: PermissionMode;
  canInitiate?: boolean;
  canReply?: boolean;
  canReceive?: boolean;
}
```

3. **Add state variables:**

```typescript
const [permissionMode, setPermissionMode] = useState<PermissionMode>(
  initialValues?.permissionMode ?? 'acceptEdits',
);
const [bypassWarningOpen, setBypassWarningOpen] = useState(false);
const [pendingPermissionMode, setPendingPermissionMode] = useState<PermissionMode | null>(null);
```

4. **Update the `useEffect` sync block** to include `permissionMode`:

Add this line inside the existing `useEffect` that syncs `initialValues`:

```typescript
setPermissionMode(initialValues.permissionMode ?? 'acceptEdits');
```

5. **Update `advancedOpen` auto-detection** to include non-default permission mode:

In both the initial `useState` call and the `useEffect` sync, add the condition:

```typescript
(initialValues?.permissionMode && initialValues.permissionMode !== 'acceptEdits')
```

The initial state:
```typescript
const [advancedOpen, setAdvancedOpen] = useState(
  !!(
    initialValues?.canInitiate ||
    initialValues?.canReply === false ||
    initialValues?.canReceive === false ||
    (initialValues?.sessionStrategy && initialValues.sessionStrategy !== 'per-chat') ||
    (initialValues?.permissionMode && initialValues.permissionMode !== 'acceptEdits')
  ),
);
```

And in the `useEffect`:
```typescript
if (
  initialValues.canInitiate ||
  initialValues.canReply === false ||
  initialValues.canReceive === false ||
  (initialValues.sessionStrategy && initialValues.sessionStrategy !== 'per-chat') ||
  (initialValues.permissionMode && initialValues.permissionMode !== 'acceptEdits')
) {
  setAdvancedOpen(true);
}
```

6. **Update `hasAdvancedChanges` badge logic:**

```typescript
const hasAdvancedChanges =
  strategy !== 'per-chat' ||
  permissionMode !== 'acceptEdits' ||
  canInitiate ||
  !canReply ||
  !canReceive;
```

7. **Update `handleConfirm` to include `permissionMode`:**

```typescript
function handleConfirm() {
  onConfirm({
    adapterId,
    agentId,
    sessionStrategy: strategy,
    label,
    chatId: chatId === SELECT_ANY ? undefined : chatId,
    channelType:
      channelType === SELECT_ANY
        ? undefined
        : (channelType as BindingFormValues['channelType']),
    permissionMode,
    canInitiate,
    canReply,
    canReceive,
  });
  if (!isEdit) {
    resetForm();
  }
}
```

8. **Update `resetForm` to reset `permissionMode`:**

```typescript
function resetForm() {
  setAdapterId('');
  setAgentId('');
  setStrategy('per-chat');
  setLabel('');
  setChatId(SELECT_ANY);
  setChannelType(SELECT_ANY);
  setChatFilterOpen(false);
  setPermissionMode('acceptEdits');
  setBypassWarningOpen(false);
  setPendingPermissionMode(null);
  setCanInitiate(false);
  setCanReply(true);
  setCanReceive(true);
  setAdvancedOpen(false);
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] `BindingFormValues` includes optional `permissionMode` field
- [ ] `permissionMode` state is initialized from `initialValues` with `'acceptEdits'` default
- [ ] `useEffect` syncs `permissionMode` when `initialValues` changes
- [ ] `advancedOpen` auto-opens when `permissionMode` is not `'acceptEdits'`
- [ ] `hasAdvancedChanges` reflects non-default `permissionMode`
- [ ] `handleConfirm` includes `permissionMode` in the submitted values
- [ ] `resetForm` resets `permissionMode` to `'acceptEdits'`
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes

Add the permission mode `Select` component inside the Advanced collapsible section of `BindingDialog`, with runtime capability filtering and a security warning AlertDialog for `bypassPermissions`.

**File:** `apps/client/src/layers/features/mesh/ui/BindingDialog.tsx`

**Implementation Steps:**

1. **Define `PERMISSION_MODE_OPTIONS` constant** (place alongside `SESSION_STRATEGIES` at the top of the file):

```typescript
import type { PermissionMode } from '@dorkos/shared/schemas';

const PERMISSION_MODE_OPTIONS: Array<{
  value: PermissionMode;
  label: string;
  description: string;
}> = [
  {
    value: 'default',
    label: 'Default',
    description: 'Agent asks for approval before using any tools',
  },
  {
    value: 'plan',
    label: 'Plan Only',
    description: 'Agent can read files but asks before making changes',
  },
  {
    value: 'acceptEdits',
    label: 'Accept Edits',
    description: 'Agent can read and write files; asks before running shell commands',
  },
  {
    value: 'bypassPermissions',
    label: 'Full Access',
    description: 'Agent can use all tools without asking for approval',
  },
];
```

2. **Add runtime capability filtering.**

The `BindingDialog` already has access to `agentsData` from `useRegisteredAgents()`. Check if `AgentManifest` includes runtime capability information. If the agent data includes `runtime` or capability information, filter the available permission modes.

For now, show all modes and filter if `supportedPermissionModes` data is available:

```typescript
// Inside the component body:
const selectedAgent = agentOptions.find((a) => a.id === agentId);
// If runtime capabilities are available through the agent data, filter modes.
// For now, show all modes â€” runtime filtering will be enhanced when
// capability data is exposed through the mesh API.
const availablePermissionModes = PERMISSION_MODE_OPTIONS;
const selectedPermissionMode = PERMISSION_MODE_OPTIONS.find((m) => m.value === permissionMode);
```

3. **Add the permission mode change handler** with `bypassPermissions` interception:

```typescript
function handlePermissionModeChange(mode: PermissionMode) {
  if (mode === 'bypassPermissions') {
    setPendingPermissionMode(mode);
    setBypassWarningOpen(true);
  } else {
    setPermissionMode(mode);
  }
}
```

4. **Add the Select component in JSX.** Place it inside the `<CollapsibleContent>` of the Advanced section, between the Session Strategy selector and the Permissions toggles:

```tsx
{/* Permission mode selector */}
<div className="space-y-1.5">
  <Label htmlFor="binding-permission-mode">Permission Mode</Label>
  <Select
    value={permissionMode}
    onValueChange={(v) => handlePermissionModeChange(v as PermissionMode)}
  >
    <SelectTrigger id="binding-permission-mode" className="w-full">
      <SelectValue />
    </SelectTrigger>
    <SelectContent>
      {availablePermissionModes.map((mode) => (
        <SelectItem key={mode.value} value={mode.value}>
          {mode.label}
        </SelectItem>
      ))}
    </SelectContent>
  </Select>
  {selectedPermissionMode && (
    <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
      {selectedPermissionMode.description}
    </p>
  )}
</div>
```

5. **Add the security warning AlertDialog.** Place it at the end of the component's JSX, before the closing `</ResponsiveDialog>` tag:

```tsx
<AlertDialog open={bypassWarningOpen} onOpenChange={setBypassWarningOpen}>
  <AlertDialogContent>
    <AlertDialogHeader>
      <AlertDialogTitle>Enable Full Access?</AlertDialogTitle>
      <AlertDialogDescription>
        Any user who can send messages through this adapter (e.g., members of your
        Slack workspace) will be able to trigger unrestricted agent actions,
        including file system access and command execution.
      </AlertDialogDescription>
    </AlertDialogHeader>
    <AlertDialogFooter>
      <AlertDialogCancel onClick={() => setPendingPermissionMode(null)}>
        Cancel
      </AlertDialogCancel>
      <AlertDialogAction
        className="bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground hover:bg-destructive/90"
        onClick={() => {
          if (pendingPermissionMode) setPermissionMode(pendingPermissionMode);
          setPendingPermissionMode(null);
        }}
      >
        Enable Full Access
      </AlertDialogAction>
    </AlertDialogFooter>
  </AlertDialogContent>
</AlertDialog>
```

Note: The `AlertDialog` components (`AlertDialog`, `AlertDialogAction`, `AlertDialogCancel`, `AlertDialogContent`, `AlertDialogDescription`, `AlertDialogFooter`, `AlertDialogHeader`, `AlertDialogTitle`) are already imported at the top of the file (used for the delete confirmation). No new imports needed for these.

